HASHITOUT ROADMAP
Vision

Develop HASHITOUT from a broad decoding and artifact discovery tool into a reproducible, evidence-driven triage platform for real-world analysis.

The goal is not to replace specialized tools, but to serve as a first-pass workbench for unknown or suspicious data.

Phase 1 - Stabilization and Signal Quality
Goals
Reduce noise
Improve trust in output
Make behavior predictable
Features
Centralized deduplication engine
Pass timing and failure visibility
Removal of duplicated logic and constants
Structured scoring model with multiple confidence factors
Outcome

Cleaner output, reduced noise, and more consistent results.

Phase 2 - Evidence and Provenance
Goals
Make every finding traceable
Enable reproducibility
Features
Provenance tracking including offsets, hashes, and source
Artifact registry system
Deterministic transform chains
JSON and JSONL export
Outcome

Findings can be traced back to their origin and reproduced reliably.

Phase 3 - Detection Intelligence
Goals
Improve usefulness outside of puzzles
Reduce bias toward readable English output
Features
Structured content detection:
JSON, XML, URLs, IPs, emails, JWTs, and similar formats
Corroboration scoring across multiple passes
Improved statistical and structural scoring
Outcome

The tool identifies meaningful structured data, not just readable text.

Phase 4 - Artifact Depth
Goals
Move beyond surface-level inspection
Features
Expanded PNG analysis including CRC checks, chunk anomalies, and LSB extraction
Expanded JPEG analysis including EXIF, segment parsing, and hidden data detection
Recursive archive analysis
Basic binary triage for formats such as PE, ELF, and PDF
Outcome

Improved detection of embedded, hidden, and layered content.

Phase 5 - Analyst Workflow
Goals
Improve usability in real investigations
Features
Decode graph model representing artifacts and transformations
Analyst notes and session persistence
Triage profiles such as ctf, triage, forensics, low-noise, and deep
Outcome

The tool becomes a structured environment for analysis rather than a one-shot utility.

Phase 6 - Field Capabilities
Goals
Support real-world investigative workflows
Features
IOC extraction including IPs, domains, emails, hashes, and related indicators
Timeline generation from file and embedded metadata
Batch and corpus analysis mode
HTML report generation
Outcome

Usable for multi-file investigations and reporting.

Phase 7 - Reliability and Trust
Goals
Ensure correctness and stability
Features
Regression test corpus
Performance benchmarking
Enforced explainability for high-confidence findings
Outcome

The tool becomes testable, stable, and trustworthy.

Guiding Principles
Deterministic over opaque
Explainable over guesswork
Signal over noise
Evidence over assumption
Designed for analyst use
End State

HASHITOUT becomes a deterministic, explainable, and reproducible triage engine for encoded, embedded, and structured data.

Not just a decoder.

A working tool for analysis.
